<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Enchanters- only play if your your intelligent (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>Edicius (WOH)</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">The problem with enchanters is you really have to be intelligent to play them.  Most people can not do it.  Hey, it is not their fault.  It is a function of the educational system.  This is my first character, I know little of dungeons yet, (as I am only level 21) but it took me little time to figure out several useful tricks.  No slash and burn (if i want that i'll play mortal combat).  I can solo yellow mobs fairly easily.  Mez, tashan, languid pace, debuffs, attack- back up let pet take a hit or two while you DOT (choke) Fear/chase the moon and your pet will follow your very afraid and very slow yellow mob slashing at it all the way while your DOTs nibble at it.  Then after your pet does some damage you can DD to aid it, this way your pet will still take the damage from the mob.  Recast fear as necessary.  (if it is a close fight heres a trick to get a few extra hits at a cost of no mana) let the damage you cause exceed that of your pet (and for god sake check on your pet now and then to make sure he doesnt die- if you do it right he shouldnt get hit that much anyway) after you allow your damage to exceed your pets the mob will turn on you, run away (dont solo yellow mobs without SOW- I shouldnt have to tell you that but JIC) your pet will chase the mob thats chasing you.  He will get a few hits in before the mob turns back to him - switch your view so you can watch the Mob following you so you know when this happens.  there ya go an extra 40-80 damage with no excess casting.  I like to turn and DD or DOT and run again- try adding 80-160 damage to a single damage spell this way and tell me ENC suck.  And ill admit if the fight is looking shaky i run like hell and leave my pet for dead.  I have only died 5 or 6 times since reaching lev 16, those are arguably some of the hardest levels ( as mentioned by Darkintellect) of the hardest Class to max.  One last comment, as someone mentioned before, how many level 50 Necros and Druids are there, and how many level 50 ENC are there?  Platinum is more valuable then gold because it is more rare.<p>

PS- I know that ENC are not meant to solo, but I do it a lot because i get exp faster by myself because everyone is always so imapatient that they end up getting themselves killed, leaving me to deal with 3 or 4 mobs.  And I hate when people loot in the middle of a fight- YOU KNOW WHO YOU ARE RETARDS- I would be a lot higher level if i didnt spend most of my time dealing in the EQ economy.  WHO WOULD LIKE TO SEE A MERCHANT CLASS.  RP isnt only about killing shit ya know.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
